      • doFilter

        public boolean doFilter(HttpRequest request,
                        HttpResponse response,
                        int req_state)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        This function will be called at time of filtering request and incase of overriding this function can be used to get the state of the request
        Parameters:
        request - - request to be filtered
        response - - response for the current request
        req_state - - can be used to get the state of the request
        Returns:
        - true-proceed, false-dont proceed further the request state might not be correct when req.getState() in http2 is called due to high frequency of callbacks
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
